cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DB 

This paper deals with designing protocols for computing statistics about sensitive data in a distributed setting, which involves topics related to cryptography (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and databases (cs.DB). The paper specifically focuses on differentially private protocols, which is a subfield of cryptography and machine learning.
